## Academic Writing Style

### Preferred Patterns

- **Nominalization**: "The analysis of data" > "Analyzing data"
- **Formal vocabulary**: "utilize" > "use", "demonstrate" > "show"
- **Objective tone**: "The results indicate" > "I think the results show"

### Patterns to Avoid

- **Colloquialisms**: "a lot of", "kind of", "pretty much"
- **Contractions**: "don't", "can't", "won't"
- **Personal opinions**: "I believe", "I feel", "In my opinion"
- **Vague quantifiers**: "some", "many", "few" (use specific numbers)

